{
  "macro_id": "cognitive-replay.filter",
  "domain": "cognitive-replay",
  "name": "filter",
  "inputs": {
    "brain": { "type": "string", "required": false, "maxLength": 80 },
    "tool": { "type": "string", "required": false, "maxLength": 80 },
    "role": { "type": "string", "required": false, "maxLength": 40 },
    "sessionId": { "type": "string", "required": false, "maxLength": 200 },
    "fromTs": { "type": "number", "required": false },
    "toTs": { "type": "number", "required": false },
    "limit": { "type": "number", "required": false }
  },
  "invariants": [
    "typeof output === 'object' && output !== null",
    "typeof output.ok === 'boolean'",
    "output.ok === false || Array.isArray(output.result.events)",
    "output.ok === false || (Number.isFinite(output.result.count) && output.result.count >= 0)",
    "output.ok === false || output.result.count <= 1000",
    "output.ok === false || Number.isFinite(output.result.totalMatching)",
    "output.ok === false || (output.result.facets && Array.isArray(output.result.facets.brains))",
    "output.ok === true || typeof (output.reason || output.error) === 'string'"
  ],
  "fuzz_cases": [
    { "input": {}, "expect": { "ok": true } },
    { "input": { "brain": "conscious" }, "expect": { "ok": true } },
    { "input": { "role": "user" }, "expect": { "ok": true } },
    { "input": { "limit": 1e308 }, "expect": { "ok": true } },
    { "input": { "brain": "<script>alert(1)</script>" }, "expect": { "ok": true } }
  ],
  "_note": "cognitive-replay.filter slices the caller's live chat-session corpus by brain/tool/role/session/date. `limit` is fail-CLOSED clamped to [1,1000] (Number(x)||300 then Math.min(1000,Math.max(1,…))). The brain/tool/role values are used only as equality filters over the corpus — an XSS probe string simply matches nothing, never executes. Facets are the deduped/sorted vocab of the caller's own corpus, so an empty corpus returns empty facet arrays with ok:true (degrade-graceful). No user-supplied value is ever written back to STATE — filter is read-only."
}
